Hi beauties! Do’t forget to tune in tonight to @entertainmenttonight
@bewellbykelly and I are sharing a glimpse of our Body by Simone App.
Thanks to the gorgeous @laurenzima 😘

@meredithfridline is one of our 8 week competition winners from NYC. Below she shares her journey of week 1 in the books!
Week 1 was FANTASTIC!! What a great feeling physically and mentally knowing that I can do this and that I made it to 3 morning classes and 2 weekend classes. My body feels great, I am sore during and after class for a little bit but it has helped me sleep well at night and be prepared for the next morning. I noticed for me that best time to go to class is in the morning and it is a great way to start my day. I have been trying to introduce myself to all the instructors at each class and let them know it was my first week so I might not be the best quite yet.

My goal for this week is try and do a double whether in the studio or at home using the BBS TV!

Yum! This is exactly what I feel like for dinner this evening. This delicious recipe and many more can be found on my new BODY BY SIMONE APP. The beautiful @bewellbykelly partnered with me to create the nutritious meal plans. Combined with challenging workouts to guide you on your health and wellness journey.
I always like to hear your feedback. I have listened and now App followers you can see an entire week of meals in advance. You can now meal prep on whichever day you choose. You can see the meals on your calendar with the little red dot. Yay! Happy eating beauties!
@pedrosallesleite

Tonight’s dinner inspiration. Roasted Brussels sprouts and squash with dried cranberries and Dijon vinaigrette. Delicious! I can’t get enough of roast vegetables. I never liked Brussels sprouts until I started cooking them in the over. Perfect on their own or add a protein.
How do you eat your veggies?
@abeautifulplate

How do brides shred for the wedding? BBS of course! Love a little Saturday dance cardio with NYC trainer @amandakloots @moshalundstrom with @repostapp.
